# LCMX Trademark Policy

**Version:** 1.0  
**Effective date:** 2026-03-05  
**Owner:** *Dirk Schoemakers*  
**Contact:** *dirk@schoemakers.com*

---

## 1. Purpose

"LCMX" and "Learning Content Metadata Exchange" are trademarks of *Dirk Schoemakers* (hereinafter "the Trademark Owner"). This policy explains who may use these marks, under what conditions, and what is prohibited.

The goal of this policy is to balance two interests:

- **Openness:** Anyone should be able to implement, extend, and build products based on the LCMX specification without asking for permission.
- **Integrity:** The name "LCMX" must reliably identify the specification maintained by the Trademark Owner. Users and implementers must be able to trust that anything called "LCMX" conforms to the official specification.

---

## 2. What the Trademarks Cover

The following are protected marks:

| Mark | Type |
|---|---|
| **LCMX** | Word mark |
| **Learning Content Metadata Exchange** | Word mark |
| **LCMX-compatible** | Certification mark |

---

## 3. Permitted Uses — No Permission Required

You may use the LCMX marks **without prior written permission** in the following cases.

### 3.1 Referring to the Specification

You may use "LCMX" to accurately refer to this specification in documentation, articles, presentations, and educational materials.

> ✅ *"This product supports the LCMX 1.0 metadata format."*  
> ✅ *"Our LMS can import and export LCMX files."*  
> ✅ *"Built with LCMX — Learning Content Metadata Exchange."*

### 3.2 Conforming Implementations

You may state that your software, product, or service is "LCMX-compatible" or "implements LCMX" if it fully conforms to the current official specification as published at the canonical repository.

### 3.3 Open Source Projects

Open source projects that implement or extend LCMX may use the mark in their project name **only** in the form `[ProjectName]-lcmx` or `lcmx-[ProjectName]` (e.g., `moodle-lcmx`, `lcmx-validator`). The project must clearly state it is not the official LCMX specification.

### 3.4 Community and Academic Use

Use in blog posts, conference talks, academic papers, and community forums to discuss or analyze LCMX is always permitted, provided the use is accurate and not misleading.

---

## 4. Prohibited Uses

The following uses are **not permitted** without explicit written permission from the Trademark Owner.

### 4.1 Competing or Forked Specifications

You may **not** publish a specification, standard, or schema under the name "LCMX" or any confusingly similar name (e.g., "LCMX2", "openLCMX", "LCMX Pro") that differs from or competes with the official LCMX specification.

If you wish to propose changes to the specification, please do so via the official repository (issues and pull requests).

### 4.2 Misleading Compatibility Claims

You may **not** claim that a product or service is "LCMX-compatible" or "LCMX-certified" if it does not fully conform to the current official specification.

### 4.3 Commercial Products Using the Mark as a Primary Identifier

You may **not** name a commercial product or service simply "LCMX" in a way that could suggest it is the official specification or is endorsed by the Trademark Owner.

> ❌ *"LCMX — the metadata platform"* (implies official product)  
> ✅ *"MetaLearn — LCMX-compatible metadata tool"* (clear third-party product)

### 4.4 Domain Names

You may **not** register domain names that use "LCMX" as the primary or sole term (e.g., `lcmx.com`, `lcmx.io`, `lcmx-standard.org`) without prior written permission.

Descriptive subdomains or paths are generally acceptable:  
> ✅ `docs.yourproduct.com/lcmx`  
> ✅ `yourproduct.com/integrations/lcmx`

---

## 5. Compatibility Requirements

To claim LCMX compatibility, an implementation must:

1. Produce and/or consume `lcmx.json` documents that validate against the official JSON Schema published at the canonical repository.
2. Not alter the semantics of any field defined in the core specification.
3. Use the `x_*` namespace prefix for any proprietary extensions (e.g., `"x_acme_custom_field": ...`).
4. Not remove or override required fields (`meta.id`, `meta.title`).

Partial implementations (e.g., supporting only `meta` and `didactics` but not `knowledge`) may still use the mark with a qualifier:

> ✅ *"Supports LCMX 1.0 (meta and didactics)"*

---

## 6. Extensions and Profiles

You are encouraged to publish extensions to the LCMX format. When doing so:

- Name your extension clearly as an extension, not a replacement: *"LCMX Healthcare Profile"*, *"LCMX Competency Extension"*.
- Prefix all custom JSON fields with `x_` followed by your namespace (e.g., `x_acme_`, `x_healthcare_`).
- Submit widely useful extensions as proposals to the official repository for potential inclusion in future versions.

---

## 7. Attribution

When distributing software or documentation that implements or references LCMX, include a notice such as:

> *"LCMX and Learning Content Metadata Exchange are trademarks of [Your Name / Organization]. This [product/document] is not affiliated with or endorsed by the Trademark Owner."*

This notice is required when the mark appears prominently (e.g., in a product name, homepage headline, or package description). It is not required for every individual mention in running text.

---

## 8. Logo and Visual Identity

If the Trademark Owner publishes an official LCMX logo, the following rules apply:

- You may use the logo to indicate compatibility, subject to the conditions in Section 3 and 5.
- You may not alter the logo's colors, proportions, or typography.
- You may not use the logo in a way that implies official endorsement or origin.

---

## 9. Reporting Misuse

If you believe someone is misusing the LCMX trademark, please report it to *[trademark@yourdomain.com]*. Include a description of the use and a link or screenshot if available. The Trademark Owner will review reports and take appropriate action.

---

## 10. Changes to This Policy

The Trademark Owner reserves the right to update this policy. Changes will be announced in the official repository. Continued use of the marks after a policy update constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.

Previous versions of this policy will be archived in the repository under `legal/trademark-policy/`.

---

## 11. Disclaimer

This policy does not grant any intellectual property rights beyond those explicitly stated. The Trademark Owner makes no warranties regarding the specification itself. This policy is not legal advice — consult a qualified attorney for specific trademark questions in your jurisdiction.

